Myself and Denise just added a note in the Upgrading Confluence documentation, that we must let the customers know.
Basically our [simplified documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Upgrading+from+Confluence+3.5+to+5.1+-+Simplified+Guide?src=search#UpgradingfromConfluence3.5to5.1-SimplifiedGuide-UpgradingConfluence] recommend to our customer, to upgrade from 3.5.X series to 5.0.3, straight due the bug on 4 series. As documentation says that we need to do upgrades incrementally across major version, but that is the following exception. So we would fix by adding this message:

{quote}
The only exception to this rule is if you are upgrading from 3.5.x to 5.0.x or above, and you have file system links in your pages. In this case, we recommend that you go directly to 5.0.3 from 3.5.x.

For more information see: CONF-23575
{quote}
