*Background Request*

As mentioned by our [Confluence 5.2 release notes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+5.2+Release+Notes], as we introduce a faster and cleaner search we removed label browser and label prioritize as describe [here|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+5.2+Release+Notes#Confluence5.2ReleaseNotes-Fasterandcleanersearch]:

{quote}Labels browser: We have removed the panel that displayed related labels on the search results page, and the search results no longer favours labels. You can still search for pages by their labels using the advanced search syntax {{labelText:chocolate.}}
{quote}

Some of our customer train their users to search Confluence using labels and categorize their information using it as they know that it would be search easily prior to Confluence release version 5.2.

This removal of feature cause customer unable to use their previous method and may need to re-organize their content in such a way so it would be easily searchable by their customer or they need to re-train their users on how to search Confluence content.

*Possible Implementation*

Re-introduce label browser panel which will display related labels might help or maybe we should provide the option to enable label browser into the search result

